reviews.review_text: Beautiful Betty Board Thanks for the update, Matt and anon!
Muchas Gracias Mateo One of my favorite shows. Thanks for the update Matt.

My first show I hitch-hiked down from Arrowbear to see the show. A great first experience. Lots of room to move around and dance. Wandered up to the stage to see the guys. I didn't even know Terrapin Station at the time and here it was the first time they played it live. I hitched back home. On the way up the hill the driver stopped to help someone but didn't set the brake. I had to leap from the back seat to jam my hand on the brake pedal as we rolled backwards down the highway. A great day all around. Scott S. S.

Wow, great show, amazing quality! Thank you so much for uploading this show. So many of my favorites. But what especially blew me away was the clarity and quality. So great. Thrilled that this is on here.

Inspiration First off I'm a 1976 fan, yes I know, but this show is beyond all my dreams.
The setlist and performance is topnotch,  what a 1st set!!! Like all my favorite songs, how can you go wrong with a Terrapin opener- BTW I love the lead is in a lower key than later versions , Estimate, Playin' >Wheel sandwich,  one of my favorite H>S>F ( Jer is smokin' on Slipnot), a Dancin' and an Eyes!!!! Heaven
